class="entry-content-section"><h3 id="american-mobile-welding" class="entry-website-title">American Mobile Welding</h3><div
class="entry-website-img"><div
class="entry-faux-browser"><div
class="entry-browser-menu"><div
class="dot"></div><div
class="dot"></div><div
class="dot"></div></div>
<picture>
<source
data-srcset="https://www.zarla.com/images/zarla-american-mobile-welding-3840x9833-20240620.webp?crop=2:1,offset-x0,offset-y0&width=332&dpr=2" media="(max-width: 412px)" />
<source
data-srcset="https://www.zarla.com/images/zarla-american-mobile-welding-3840x9833-20240620.webp?crop=400:248,offset-x0,offset-y0&width=495&dpr=2" media="(max-width: 575px)" />
<img
class="lazyload"
data-src="https://www.zarla.com/images/zarla-american-mobile-welding-3840x9833-20240620.webp?crop=400:248,offset-x0,offset-y0&width=650&dpr=2"
width="650"
height="403"
alt="desktop screenshot of website American Mobile Welding"
/>
</picture></div></div><p
class="entry-website-detail website-detail-url">
<span
class="icon">
<img
src="/assets/images/icon-link.svg" alt="chain icon" width="29" height="29" />
</span>
<a
class="force-single-line" href="https://www.americanmobileweld.com/" target="_blank" rel="noopener nofollow">
https://www.americanmobileweld.com/
</a></p><p
class="entry-website-detail website-detail-location">
<span
class="icon">
<img
src="/assets/images/icon-pin.svg" alt="pin icon" width="30" height="30" />
</span>
<span>Concord, California, U.S.</span></p><div
class="entry-text"><p>American Mobile Welding are mobile welding specialists offering a wide range of residential and industrial welding services throughout California. The website's bright color scheme offsets the serious tone of the theme and, along with high-quality color images, creates a memorable visual appeal.</p><p>The prominent headings emphasizing the company's 24-hour response policy and on-call services effectively highlight its customer-first ethos. However, the website is missing certain important content, such as client reviews and a portfolio of completed projects.</p></div><h4>Pros and Cons</h4><div
class="entry-indented-box"><div
class="entry-website-pros">
<span
class="icon icon-sm">
<img
src="/assets/images/icon-plus.svg" alt="plus sign" width="18" height="18" />
</span><div
class="entry-text"><p>The website's contact options are prominently displayed and encourage user engagement with clear CTA buttons. The "Certifications" section conveys a sense of authority and trustworthiness, and WAVE indicates no contrast errors on the site.</p></div></div><div
class="entry-website-cons">
<span
class="icon icon-sm">
<img
src="/assets/images/icon-minus.svg" alt="minus sign" width="18" height="18" />
</span><div
class="entry-text"><p>The use of more personable imagery rather than stock images would enhance the site's overall appeal. According to Google's PageSpeed Insights test, the website's pages load slowly on both desktop and mobile.</p></div></div></div><h4>Desktop Review</h4><div
class="entry-website-desktop"><div
data-src="https://www.zarla.com/images/zarla-american-mobile-welding-3840x9833-20240620.webp"
data-type="desktop"
class="lightbox-trigger js-lightbox-trigger"
><div
class="lightbox-thumbnail">
<img
class="lazyload"
data-src="https://www.zarla.com/images/zarla-american-mobile-welding-3840x9833-20240620.webp?crop=400:248,offset-x0,offset-y0&width=400&dpr=2"
alt="desktop screenshot of website"
width="400"
height="248"
/></div>
<img
class="lightbox-thumbnail-magnifier"
src="/assets/images/icon-magnifying.svg"
alt="magnifying glass"
width="50"
height="50"
/></div><div
class="entry-text"><p>The desktop version displays effectively with good navigation options that give visitors insight into the company's mission, industry specializations, and career opportunities. Optimal readability is also ensured with large headings introducing legible content sections. On Google's PageSpeed Insights test, the site has a decent performance score of 84/100, but page loading times are quite slow.</p></div></div><h4>Mobile Review</h4><div
class="entry-website-mobile"><div
data-src="https://www.zarla.com/images/zarla-american-mobile-welding-824x16382-20240620.webp"
data-type="mobile"
class="lightbox-trigger js-lightbox-trigger"
><div
class="lightbox-thumbnail">
<img
class="lazyload"
data-src="https://www.zarla.com/images/zarla-american-mobile-welding-824x16382-20240620.webp?crop=3:5,offset-x0,offset-y0&width=375&dpr=2"
alt="mobile screenshot of website"
width="325"
height="542"
/></div>
<img
class="lightbox-thumbnail-magnifier"
src="/assets/images/icon-magnifying.svg"
alt="magnifying glass"
width="50"
height="50"
/></div><div
class="entry-text"><p>The mobile site retains its high-quality and professional appeal with large headings and well-spaced content that covers the company's services and industry accreditations. However, some of the contact details get hidden behind the hamburger menu, and should rather be displayed in the top menu bar for more prominence. Contrary to real-world experience, the site's performance score is rather low at 35/100.</p></div></div></div></div></div></div><div
class="entry-container entry-container-content"><div
class="entry-content-wrapper"><div
